=\"fn\">x</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Operations.html#Set.preimage\">⁻¹'</a> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Singleton.singleton\">{</a><span class=\"fn\">y</span><a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Singleton.singleton\">}</a>, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ <span class=\"fn\">x₀</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Operations.html#Set.preimage\">⁻¹'</a> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Singleton.singleton\">{</a><span class=\"fn\">y₀</span><a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Singleton.singleton\">}</a>, <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Frequently\">∃ᶠ</a> (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">X</span>) <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Frequently\">in</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">x₀</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Frequently\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Assume `f` is a closed map. If there are points `y` arbitrarily close to `y₀` such that `p`\nholds for at least some `x ∈ f ⁻¹' {y}`, then one can find `x₀ ∈ f ⁻¹' {y₀}` such that there\nare points `x` arbitrarily close to `x₀` which satisfy `p`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Maps/Basic.html#IsClosedMap.frequently_nhds_fiber","kind":"theorem","line":579,"name":"IsClosedMap.frequently_nhds_fiber","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Topology/Maps/Basic.lean#L579-L592"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Maps/Basic.html#IsClosedMap.eventually_nhds_fibe